
## 🧭 Project Overview

In this project, we use **Terraform** to create an **AWS Security Group**, which acts as a virtual firewall for Amazon EC2 instances. Instead of manually configuring firewall rules through the AWS Management Console, 
we define the security group using Infrastructure as Code (IaC), making the configuration repeatable, version-controlled, and easy to maintain.

This project introduces one of the most important networking concepts in AWS: **controlling inbound and outbound traffic to cloud resources**.

---

## 🎯 Objective

* Create an AWS Security Group using Terraform
* Configure inbound (ingress) rules
* Configure outbound (egress) rules
* Understand the role of Security Groups in AWS networking
* Learn how Terraform manages network security declaratively

