## 🔐 Security Best Practices

* Avoid allowing SSH (`22`) from `0.0.0.0/0` in production.
* Restrict SSH access to trusted IP addresses or VPNs.
* Open only the ports required by the application.
* Use separate Security Groups for different application tiers.
* Regularly audit Security Group rules for unnecessary access.

---

## 🏗️ Real-World Use Cases

| Scenario            | Description                                   |
| ------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Web Servers         | Allow HTTP (80) and HTTPS (443) traffic       |
| Application Servers | Permit traffic only from load balancers       |
| Database Servers    | Restrict access to application servers only   |
| Bastion Hosts       | Allow SSH from trusted administrator IPs      |
| Internal Services   | Control communication between private subnets |

---

## ⚠️ Common Mistakes

* ❌ Opening all ports (`0-65535`) unnecessarily
* ❌ Allowing unrestricted SSH access (`0.0.0.0/0`) in production
* ❌ Forgetting outbound rules required for updates
* ❌ Creating duplicate Security Groups with overlapping rules
* ❌ Hardcoding values instead of using Terraform variables

