## 💡 Senior DevOps Insight

One of the biggest differences between a beginner and an experienced cloud engineer is how they think about security.

A beginner often asks:

> "How do I make my server accessible?"

An experienced DevOps engineer asks:

> "Who should have access, on which ports, from where, and why?"

Security Groups embody this mindset. Every rule should have a clear purpose and follow the **principle of least privilege**, exposing only the services necessary for the application to function securely.
